@justschen this CSS rule applies to all glyph margin widgets, maybe you want to scope it more specifically for the lightbulb widget?

https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/31f831310c643ae03c4b84124b5a427d0bed0483/src/vs/editor/contrib/codeAction/browser/lightBulbWidget.css#L48-L53

This is overriding what was the [default styling](https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/blob/31f831310c643ae03c4b84124b5a427d0bed0483/src/vs/editor/browser/viewParts/glyphMargin/glyphMargin.css#L11-L20) for glyph margin widgets.

Workaround:

```ts
try {
    await rm(path, {...});
} catch (e) {
    if ('code' in e && e.code === 'ELOOP') {
         await unlink(p);
     }
}
```

